# Crayon Cosmos Design System

EduVisualsPH has ONE design system: **Crayon Cosmos** (warm storybook lab — cream
paper, crayon accents, Fredoka/Nunito, rounded shapes) plus a hand-drawn SVG art
framework. Theme `crayon` is defined in `src/index.css` and is the only theme.
Full docs: `docs/design-system/crayon.md`.

## Using crayon art

```tsx
import { CrayonArt } from '../components/crayon';
<CrayonArt name="beaker" size={34} color="sky" animate="draw" />
```

- Art auto-discovered from `src/assets/crayon/<category>/<name>.svg` (icons,
  spots, flourishes, accents). `name` = file name without `.svg`.
- Props: `name`, `size`/`width`/`height`, `color` (ink|sky|berry|sunshine|leaf|grape|paper),
  `animate` (none|draw|wiggle), `title` (omit => decorative/aria-hidden).
- Subject icons: `crayonArtForTags(tags)` from `../components/crayon/subjectArt`.
- Preview all art at the `/crayon` route.

## Adding new art (drop-in, no wiring)

Create `src/assets/crayon/<category>/<kebab-name>.svg` to spec:
- `viewBox="0 0 100 100"`, NO width/height on the root `<svg>`.
- Colors via classes only (never hardcoded hex): `crayon-fill-*` /
  `crayon-stroke-*` / `crayon-ink`, or `currentColor` to follow the `color` prop.
- Crayon feel: round caps/joins, chunky stroke-width (~5), slightly wobbly paths.
- Self-drawing strokes: add `pathLength="1"` + class `crayon-draw`.

## Rules

- Crayon art is decoration/illustration ONLY — never over data, inputs, or
  visualizer canvases; keep those crisp and legible.
- Default art to decorative (no `title`); add `title` only for meaningful images.
- Don't reintroduce other themes (Stardust/Pop Lab were retired) or hardcode
  colors — use DaisyUI semantic tokens + the crayon color classes.
- Motion must respect `prefers-reduced-motion` (already handled globally).
